The winner of the 2021 BBNaija shows Whitemoney is set to return to a root that played a crucial role in his growth. The reality TV star while on the show said he once worked as a conductor under Ojuelegba bridge as his abode every night. In a bid to appreciate the role played by the place and people there, the Kaduna-born singer has said he will be visiting the same location after many years to celebrate with them.   TV actor Morgan Stevens found dead in kitchen     Ex-BBN’s Kiddwaya: My woman must have big heart     My sister is adored more than me – DJ Cuppy   He made this known via an Instagram post where he shared a sticker displaying the details of the anticipated visit. - Advertisement - Whitemoney captioned the post: “OJUELEGBA STAND UP!!!! It’s about time and I literally can’t wait to be with you all on the 28th day of January 2022. “You already know how we roll, we are going to catch up, vibeeeee and have undiluted fun. “Stay ready so you don’t have to get readyyyyyyy. See you sooooooooooon.”